bug.short_desc: [MediaWiki] Support markups and tags in pre-formatted blocks.

long_desc.thetext:
Build Identifier: There is two methods to create a pre-formatted block in a MediaWiki instance: 1. Including the content between a pre tag: 
 ....
2. Using indentation (one space a the beginning of each block line). With method 1, other HTML tags contained in the block will be converted with HTML-entities (< and >) to appear as plain text in the block and wiki markup is ignored. http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Help:HTML_in_wikitext#Pre or http://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Help:Formatting#HTML_tags (see Completely preformatted text) With method 2, it is possible to add wiki markup that is processed. The allowed HTML tags are not converted like for plain text. http://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Help:Formatting#Text_formatting_markup (see: Preformatted text) Reproducible: Always
